15:43.443 --> 15:45.404
[Funk music playing]

15:50.033 --> 15:52.119
Oh, you out of time, baby.

16:03.130 --> 16:04.214
Damn!

16:04.464 --> 16:06.884
ANNOUNCER: Rufus Griffin stars in...

16:07.009 --> 16:08.802
...Black to the Future.

16:09.052 --> 16:12.723
We're talking Marty McSuperfly, dig?

16:12.890 --> 16:16.143
Marty, I want to be your fine,
sweet-ass bitch.

16:16.810 --> 16:18.937
Damn! Brother done kissed his mama!

16:20.063 --> 16:21.857
[Playing funk music]

16:23.901 --> 16:25.819
ANNOUNCER: Oh, yeah.

16:29.281 --> 16:31.033
Get me Isaac Hayes.

16:31.116 --> 16:33.744
Isaac, you know that new sound
you been looking for?

16:33.827 --> 16:35.495
Well, listen to this!

16:39.917 --> 16:42.461
Come on, Lois.
Stop being such a stick in the mud.

16:42.544 --> 16:44.046
I'm giving these saps hope.

16:44.129 --> 16:46.590
And I'm getting the house
painted for free.

16:46.673 --> 16:49.009
It's win-freakin'-win, baby.

16:50.427 --> 16:52.596
[Cheery instrumental music]

16:55.766 --> 16:57.267
Hey, flathead, chop-chop.

16:58.101 --> 16:59.228
[Exclaiming]

16:59.311 --> 17:00.771
[Sighing]

17:00.938 --> 17:02.481
Hey, great job on the lawn.

17:02.564 --> 17:05.817
Now do it again,
and this time leave it a little longer.

17:05.901 --> 17:09.071
CHRIS: Hey, Dad. Hurry up.
You're missing Gumbel 2 Gumbel.

17:09.154 --> 17:11.782
They caught the guy,
and now they're interviewing him.

17:13.242 --> 17:16.537
Purse snatching, society's fault,
or one man's cry for help?

17:16.620 --> 17:19.373
What are you talking about?
I wanted her freakin' money.

17:19.456 --> 17:20.999
[Bryant grunting]

17:39.184 --> 17:41.478
What the hell's wrong with him?

17:41.562 --> 17:42.896
[Bryant grunting]

17:43.146 --> 17:45.858
Some other time, Chris.
Now, where's my shoes?

17:51.864 --> 17:53.198
[Sighing]

17:55.158 --> 17:57.160
These people are worshipping you.

17:57.244 --> 17:59.788
Don't you think there's someone
who might resent that?

17:59.872 --> 18:02.332
A being who's all-knowing
and all-powerful?

18:02.416 --> 18:04.710
Someone's got a pretty high
opinion of herself.

18:04.793 --> 18:08.046
Not me, Peter. God. The real God.

18:08.130 --> 18:09.381
What's the big deal?

18:09.464 --> 18:12.092
So I told a little fib,
and now people think I'm God.

18:12.176 --> 18:14.511
When did God ever say
He didn't want someone else...

18:14.595 --> 18:15.846
...being worshipped like Him?

18:15.929 --> 18:17.681
It's one of the Ten Commandments.

18:17.764 --> 18:21.768
Come on. Those were written,
like, 200 years ago. Times have changed!

18:21.852 --> 18:22.853
[Lois screams]

18:22.936 --> 18:24.771
PETER: Okay, let's stay calm.

18:25.480 --> 18:29.151
Lois, if you're scared, I'll hold you
until the lights are on again.

18:29.234 --> 18:31.195
CHRIS: Dad, it's me.
PETER: Go to your room.

18:32.529 --> 18:34.781
That's the last of them.

18:34.865 --> 18:39.036
I still don't know how every light bulb
could go out at the same time.

18:39.369 --> 18:40.412
Oh, my God.

18:40.495 --> 18:41.580
Yes?

18:41.663 --> 18:43.248
That's not funny.

18:43.332 --> 18:46.877
Those fanatics are building
a golden idol of you on our lawn.

18:49.213 --> 18:51.632
I look like a freakin' Emmy.

18:51.965 --> 18:53.091
Hint-hint.

18:53.300 --> 18:54.927
Damn it to hell!

18:55.219 --> 18:58.013
This is embarrassing.
I seem to have fleas.

18:58.096 --> 18:59.640
That's never happened before.

18:59.723 --> 19:00.724
CHRIS: Morning.

19:01.600 --> 19:03.852
PETER: Chris, puberty hit you
like a ton of bricks.

19:03.936 --> 19:05.395
What do you mean?

19:05.562 --> 19:07.481
Don't you see what's happening?

19:07.564 --> 19:09.107
Of course I do, Lois.

19:09.191 --> 19:12.152
Our fresh-faced little boy
is becoming a pock-marked...

19:12.236 --> 19:15.405
...hideously disfigured man.
Sunrise. Sunset.

19:15.489 --> 19:18.617
No. The light bulbs last night,
my fleas, Chris' pimples.

19:18.700 --> 19:20.911
They're just like darkness,
gadflies, and boils.

19:20.994 --> 19:24.498
Three of the plagues God visited upon
Egypt in the Old Testament.

19:24.581 --> 19:27.501
Come on, there's a logical explanation
for all those things.

19:27.584 --> 19:29.503
There was a power surge,
you don't bathe...

19:29.586 --> 19:32.297
...and Chris has had acne problems
since the fourth grade.

19:32.381 --> 19:35.259
The kids were all calling him Crisco
and Pizza Face...

19:35.342 --> 19:38.220
...and Rootin'-Tootin' Raspberry.
Remember, Chris?

19:38.303 --> 19:39.513
Now I do.

19:39.596 --> 19:40.848
[Crying]

19:40.931 --> 19:42.182
[Meg screams]

19:42.474 --> 19:44.059
Meg, what's wrong?

19:44.142 --> 19:46.103
I was giving Stewie a bath, and....

19:47.020 --> 19:50.107
Trust me, Meg, at his age,
it's strictly involuntary.

19:50.190 --> 19:53.485
No! The water,
it turned all red and goopy, like blood!

19:53.569 --> 19:54.570
Blood?

19:54.736 --> 19:58.949
How positively delightful.
It's as if someone stabbed Mr. Bubble!

19:59.116 --> 20:00.367
My baby!

20:00.534 --> 20:02.619
Get out there
and tell those people the truth.

20:02.703 --> 20:06.832
Make them stop worshipping you
before it starts hailing in my house!

20:07.124 --> 20:09.751
There's gotta be an
explanation for all this!

20:09.835 --> 20:13.463
You want an explanation? God is pissed!

20:13.964 --> 20:15.799
Let's get out of here!

20:15.966 --> 20:17.885
[Eerie instrumental music]

20:19.469 --> 20:21.388
[Sinister instrumental music]

20:21.555 --> 20:24.349
Stop it! Stop worshipping me!

20:24.433 --> 20:26.185
I'm just a big fake...

20:26.268 --> 20:30.731
...like the moon landing
and Marky Mark's hog in Boogie Nights...

20:30.898 --> 20:33.025
...and Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman!

20:33.317 --> 20:36.111
I don't mean
that completely untrue gay rumor.

20:36.195 --> 20:39.364
They're just both really phony,
just like me.

20:39.448 --> 20:42.367
I'm sorry, okay? Now make it stop.

20:44.703 --> 20:45.954
[All screaming]

20:46.038 --> 20:47.539
This is the final plague!

20:47.623 --> 20:49.291
Good, it's starting to get really old.

20:49.374 --> 20:51.919
The final plague is
the death of the first-born son.

20:52.002 --> 20:54.296
-No! Stewie!
-The first-born son.

20:54.379 --> 20:55.797
-Meg.
-Your wife.

20:55.881 --> 20:57.049
Chris!

20:58.383 --> 21:00.052
Oh, my God. Are you okay?

21:00.135 --> 21:03.764
Hey, Dad, I can see a white light
at the end of a long tunnel.

21:03.847 --> 21:06.975
Oh, that's great, son.
Light is good. Run towards the light.

21:07.059 --> 21:09.353
No! Run away from the light!

21:09.436 --> 21:13.148
Hey, Dad, do you think they got
Gumbel 2 Gumbel in heaven?

21:14.066 --> 21:16.944
Yes, son, and there's no reruns
or commercials...

21:17.027 --> 21:18.904
...and Kirstie Alley is still hot...

21:18.987 --> 21:22.199
...and all those scrambled channels
come in clear as a bell.

21:22.282 --> 21:24.409
Please don't take him, God. I'm sorry.

21:26.453 --> 21:28.413
We think the Griffin guy gets it.

21:28.497 --> 21:31.291
Good, good.
Peggy, turn off the plagues, please.

21:31.375 --> 21:33.252
PEGGY: Yes, sir, Mr. Patterson.

21:33.627 --> 21:35.003
She's new.

21:36.547 --> 21:39.091
[Awe-inspiring instrumental music]

21:39.925 --> 21:41.426
I think the plagues went away.

21:41.510 --> 21:44.137
-So did the white light.
-Oh, honey!

21:44.721 --> 21:47.099
Thank God! I mean, thank me!

21:48.392 --> 21:50.352
Kidding! It was a joke!

21:50.435 --> 21:51.603
[Frog croaking]

21:53.689 --> 21:55.190
[Theme music]
